Moslem militants in Jammu-Kashmir State were involved in several incidents on  Wednesday, killing three soldiers in a truck with a bomb, shooting a suspected informer,  and engaging in three sniper battles.
These attacks came amid Indian government claims  of the arrest of 12 leaders of Hezbul Mujahedeen, a Moslem militant group.
The state  governor has vowed to neutralize the "anti-national elements," saying it may take up to a  year.
India's leading national parties have decided to send a high-powered delegation to  the capital, Srinagar.
Kashmir has been a problem between Pakistan and India for 40  years and precipitated two wars. 
